  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Deadlock in Multicore when we use Spinlock"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "An example for deadlock in multicore"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task A and Task B runs in Core 0 -> Task A has highest priority"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task C runs in Core 1"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Deadlock%20Use%20Case%201%20-%20Preemptive%20Task%20in%20Same%20Core/image2022-8-10_18-2-52.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Deadlock Use Case 1 - Preemptive Task in Same Core/image2022-8-10_18-2-52.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Solution to Deadlock problem"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use Spinlock with interrupt lock mechanism"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task A preemption is stopped since interrupts are locked"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Deadlock%20Use%20Case%201%20-%20Preemptive%20Task%20in%20Same%20Core/image2022-8-10_18-6-33.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Deadlock Use Case 1 - Preemptive Task in Same Core/image2022-8-10_18-6-33.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If a task in the same core uses spinlock for a shared data, then make sure Spinlock is combined with interrupt lock"
    }
  ],
